<L>And open every &s;eal?</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<HEAD><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"></HEAD>
<L>He &s;hall accompli&s;h thy decrees,</L>
<L>And all thy wonders tell;</L>
<L>Lo! in his &s;overeign hand, the keys</L>
<L>Of heaven, and death, and hell.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<HEAD><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"></HEAD>
<L>He hath redeem'd our &s;ouls with blood,</L>
<L>Hath broke the pri&s;oners chain;</L>
<L>Hath made us kings and prie&s;ts with GOD,</L>
<L>And we with him &s;hall reign.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="6">
<HEAD>6</HEAD>
<L>Now, to the Lamb, that once was &s;lain,</L>
<L>Be endle&s;s ble&s;&s;ings paid;</L>
<L>While &s;aints and angels fill his train,</L>
<L>And glories crown his head.</L>
</LG>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="hymn">
<HEAD>HYMN II. The nativity of <HI>Chri&s;t. Luke i.30. &amp;c. ii.10.</HI></HEAD>
<LG>
<HEAD><GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"></HEAD>
